Method Detail

decompose

public Result<java.util.List<TspTask.City>> decompose()
Implements the decompose phase of TSP divide and conquer solution. Every task calculates its new lower-bound initially and checks if it is lesser than the existing upper-bound. If yes, then the task continues with the decomposition. A solution and a new upper-bound are computed if the task is the last node in the decomposition tree (or) the decomposition has reached an internal restricted recursion depth. The new upper-bound is communicated to the compute space. Else, this node in the search tree is not explored further and it is pruned.

Specified by:
decompose in interface Task<java.util.List<TspTask.City>>
Returns:
A Result object containing either subtasks that have been created during this decomposition stage, or value of a base case in the underlying recursion

compose

public Result<java.util.List<TspTask.City>> compose(java.util.List<?> list)
Implements the conquer phase of TSP divide and conquer solution. Used by the successor of each task to integrate the routes returned by all its children and find the least cost route from all of them.

Specified by:
compose in interface Task<java.util.List<TspTask.City>>
Parameters:
list - A java.util.List containing results obtained from the smaller subtasks that were originally generated by the same task
Returns:
A Result object containing a value obtained by composing results of smaller subtasks that were generated by this task in the 'Divide' phase
